{"word":"πικρότης","slug":"πικρότης","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>πικρότης</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>from <a href='S:πικρός'><el>πικρός</el></a>\n<el>(πικρότης, ητος, ἡ,) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>pungency, bitterness</i>, of taste, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>bitterness, cruelty</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}